@subsubsection Inexact real comparators


@defun make-inexact-real-comparator @var{epsilon} @var{rounding} @var{nan-handling}
Return a comparator that compares inexact real numbers including NaNs as
follows: if after rounding to the nearest @var{epsilon} they are the
same, they compare equal; otherwise they compare as specified by
@func{<}.

The direction of rounding is specified by the @var{rounding} argument,
which is either a procedure accepting two arguments (the number and
@var{epsilon}), or else one of the symbols @code{floor}, @code{ceiling},
@code{truncate}, or @code{round}.

The value of @var{epsilon} is used by the generated comparator only if
@var{rounding} is a procedure: it is ignored if @var{rounding} is a
symbol.  When @var{epsilon} is not @false{} and @var{rounding} is a
symbol: this function raises a @strong{continuable} exception with
compound condition object of types:
@condition{inexact-real-comparator-with-unused-epsilon},
@condition{who}, @condition{message}, @condition{irritants}.

The argument @var{nan-handling} specifies how to compare NaN arguments
to non--NaN arguments.

@itemize
@item
If it is a procedure: the procedure is invoked on the other argument if
either argument is a NaN.

@item
If it is the symbol @code{min}: NaN values precede all other values.

@item
If it is the symbol @code{max}: NaN values follow all other values.

@item
If it is the symbol @code{error}: an error is signalled if a NaN value
is compared by raising a non--continuable exception with compound
condition object of types: @condition{who}, @condition{message},
@condition{irritants}, @condition{comparator-nan-comparison-error}.

@item
If both arguments are NaNs: they always compare as equal.
@end itemize
@end defun


Here is an example of comparator using the @code{round} rounding mode
and the @code{error} policy to compare @code{+nan.0}:

@lisp
#!vicare
(import (vicare) (srfi :114))

(define-constant C
  (make-inexact-real-comparator #f 'round 'error))

;; type test
(comparator-test-type C 1.2)    @result{} #t
(comparator-test-type C "ciao") @result{} #f
(comparator-test-type C 1+2i)   @result{} #f

;; type check
(comparator-check-type C 1.2)   @result{} #t
(try
    (comparator-check-type C (void))
  (catch E
    ((&comparator-type-error)
     #t)
    (else #f)))
@result{} #t

;; comparison
(comparator-compare C 1.2 1.2)          @result{}  0
(comparator-compare C 1.0 2.0)          @result{} -1
(comparator-compare C 2.0 1.0)          @result{} +1

(comparator-compare C +inf.0 +inf.0)    @result{} 0
(comparator-compare C -inf.0 -inf.0)    @result{} 0
(comparator-compare C -inf.0 +inf.0)    @result{} -1
(comparator-compare C +inf.0 -inf.0)    @result{} +1

(comparator-compare C +nan.0 +nan.0)    @result{} 0
(try
    (comparator-compare C +nan.0 1.0)
  (catch E
    ((&comparator-nan-comparison-error)
     #t)
    (else E)))
@result{} #t
(try
    (comparator-compare C 1.0 +nan.0)
  (catch E
    ((&comparator-nan-comparison-error)
     #t)
    (else E)))
@result{} #t

;; comparison with rounding
(comparator-compare C 1.04 1.0) @result{} 0
(comparator-compare C 0.96 1.0) @result{} 0

;; hash
(= (comparator-hash C 1.0) (comparator-hash C 1.04))      @result{} #t
(= (comparator-hash C 1.0) (comparator-hash C 0.96))      @result{} #t
(non-negative-exact-integer? (comparator-hash C +inf.0))  @result{} #t
(non-negative-exact-integer? (comparator-hash C -inf.0))  @result{} #t
(non-negative-exact-integer? (comparator-hash C +nan.0))  @result{} #t
@end lisp

